- ## DevOps
#DevOps 
DevOps is a relatively new term that appeared a decade ago [7]. Initially it was a word to explain the need of collaboration between development (DEV) and operations (OPS) teams. DevOps does not have a single generally adopted definition and many companies understand it differently [8]. For instance, possible definitions are “a way of collaboration in which processes are automated as much as possible”
